South Africa has recorded 2 355 new coronavirus infections in the last 24-hour cycle, taking the total number to 1 617 840. The country has also recorded 80 new COVID-19 related fatalities on Tuesday. This brings the total number of deaths to 55 340. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in Gauteng. “Regrettably, we report 80 more COVID-19 related deaths: Eastern Cape 6, Free State 22, Gauteng 32, Kwa-Zulu Natal 5, Limpopo 6, Mpumalanga 0, North West 0, Northern Cape 0 and Western Cape 9,” says Dr Mkhize. Recoveries stand at 1 527 968. The cumulative number of tests conducted to date is 11 166 950. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 1 617 840 the total number of deaths is 55 340 the total number of recoveries is 1 527 968 and the total number of vaccines administered is 519 139. pic.twitter.com/rCM13Fbfv6 — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) May 18, 2021 